# Short Prompt Mapping

Map intent to first-class commands in 1-2 calls.

Examples:
- "List pages" -> `pages.list`
- "Show widgets on login" -> `widgets.list {nameOrId:"login"}`
- "All text fields on login" -> `textfields.list {nameOrId:"login"}`
- "Get this widget" -> `widget.get {nameOrId:<page>, nodeId:<id>}`
- "Change text on this widget" -> `widget.set {nameOrId:<page>, nodeId:<id>, text:"..."}`
- "Create a button under this container" -> `widget.insert` or `widget.create`
- "Remove widget id-Button_x on onboarding" -> `widget.delete`
- "Rename Onboarding to Intro" -> `page.update`
- "Refresh snapshot from FlutterFlow" -> `snapshots.refresh {mode:"incremental", fetchStrategy:"auto"}`
- "Refresh full snapshot in chunks" -> `snapshots.refresh {mode:"full", fetchStrategy:"file", maxFetch:5}`
- "Try safe apply under rate limits" -> `changeset.applySafe {changesetId:"...", confirm:true}`

Always return resolved IDs and fileKeys in response summaries.
